oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: D.R. Johnson Grocery Store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of several unidentified men sitting on the front porch of D.R. Johnson Grocery Store in Mount Joy, Tennessee. A single gasoline pump and a sign for Coca Cola are visible outside the shop. David Richard ""Dick"" Johnson (1911-1967) of Mount Pleasant owned the store.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stores & shops; Men; Gasoline pumps
